knowledge_graph.title: Film Forum
knowledge_graph.type: Movie theater in New York City, New York
knowledge_graph.description: Film Forum is a nonprofit movie theater at 209 West Houston Street in Greenwich Village, Manhattan. It began in 1970 as an alternative screening space for independent films, with 50 folding chairs, one projector and a $19,000 annual budget. Karen Cooper became director in 1972.

user_reviews.summary: Has good film selection, old fashioned movie theater style, and good snack bar

The staff are friendly and helpful and the place is well kept.
